               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430612-name-1718" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1718" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1718" type="surname" value="CAMPBELL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1718" type="given" value="HENRY EDWARD"></interp>HENRY EDWARD CAMPBELL</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a painter, and live in Dartmouth-street. I was at Greenwich fair on Tuesday, the 6th of June—I had two handkerchiefs—I missed one when the officer informed me—this is it—it is soiled with paint—I did not see the prisoner till he was in custody.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430612-name-1719" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1719" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1719" type="surname" value="CARPENTER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1719" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN CARPENTER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a policeman. About half-past nine o'clock on Tuesday night I was on duty in the fair, and saw the prisoner go behind two gentlemen, who were looking at Richardson's show—the gentlemen moved</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184306120240"></xptr>
               <p>on about twenty yards, and I saw the handkerchief hanging out of the prose<lb></lb>cutor's pocket—the prisoner then went up, took the handkerchief out, and was walking away, when I took him with it, and told the prosecutor—I found this other handkerchief round the prisoner's neck, and these white gloves, a key, and kaleidescope on him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> It was not me that took the handkerchief, it was a young <hi rend="italic">chap</hi> who stood before me; he ran through the mob, and the policeman took me; they picked the handkerchief off the ground. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> He said nothing of the sort till his second examination—there was no second person near him—I have made inquiries, and find he bore a good character up to three weeks ago.</p>
               <p>
